Using:
    pip3
    Python3.9.6
    venv

venv instruction:
    install venv:
        pip3 install virtualenv
    create venv folder:
        virtualenv <name>
    activate venv:
        source <name>/bin/activate 
        pip3 install -r requirements.txt
    exit venv:
        deactivate

Setup:
    In API folder create .env file: Example below
        HOST = "127.0.0.1"
        PORT = "5000"
        ATLAS_URI= "tbd"
        DB_NAME= "tbd"
        DEFINITION_TAG= "definitions"
        DEFINITION_PREFIX= "/definition"
        LLM_TAG= "llm"
        LLM_PREFIX="/llm"
    To start run:
        main.py
    To see api documentation go to:
        http://<host>:<port>/docs#/